At a workplace and its environment, several different risks could occur and be a danger for the safety
and health of the employees or potential loss of assets.
This standard applies to the systematic risk assessment of all possible hazards at the workplace and in
the workplace environment of natural gas systems including relevant outcome of natural gas use, so that
the risk is reduced.
This standard applies to the documentation relevant to the risk assessment information for the
verification dossier.
The following are not included in the scope of the current edition of this Israeli Standard:
o Natural gas consuming appliances pertaining to the domestic sector;
o Appliances solely driven by fuel oil, or other fuel gases, e.g. LPG or biogas;

Natural gas consuming appliances pertaining to the domestic sector;
o Appliances solely driven by fuel oil, or other fuel gases, e.g. LPG or biogas;
o Heating Recovery Steam Generators (HRSGs);
o Gas turbines, gas engines and CHP (Combined Heat and Power);
o Risks that are not resulted by the conversion of the IAA to natural gas (i.e., risk assessment
procedures to assess risks which are not resulted from natural gas systems, or the environment
of these natural gas systems, are not included);
o Managing the IAA construction, installation and its inspection (performed by the End-User and
inspected by the Ministry of Labor, Welfare and Social Services);
o Occupational and health issues (in the area of responsibility of the Ministry of Labor, Welfare
and Social Services);
o Issues in the area of responsibility of the Ministry of Environmental Protection, e.g. the quality
of the flue gases emissions;
o Issues not in the area of responsibility of the Natural Gas authority in the Ministry of National
Infrastructures, Energy and Water Resources, e.g. energy performance of the appliances.
